  "text": "• Ciguatera: Ciguatera is the most frequently observed form of tropical fish poisoning. It blocks the sodium channel leading to slowed nerve conduction and causes the peripheral and central nervous system symptoms such as facial paresthesia, myalgia, cramps and weakness. Ciguatera poisoning leads to the gastrointestinal and cardiovascular disturbances too [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
